  "prompt": "Where is the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near or on University of Washington campus?",
  "response": "Finding the cheapest place to buy vitamin B-12 near or on the University of Washington (UW) campus depends on availability and current pricing, but here are some options to consider:\n\n1. **UW Campus Pharmacies**:  \n   The UW Medical Center or Hall Health Center (on campus) may carry vitamin supplements at reasonable prices. Check directly with their pharmacy for availability and pricing.\n\n2. **Local Grocery Stores**:  \n   - **Trader Joe's** (University Village): Known for affordable supplements.  \n   - **QFC** (University Village): Offers generic and branded vitamins.  \n   - **Safeway** (Roosevelt Square): Often has sales on vitamins and supplements.\n\n3. **Drugstores**:  \n   - **Bartell Drugs** (University Village or Downtown Seattle): Check for deals on their generic brands.  \n   - **Walgreens** (University District): Often has discounts on supplements.  \n   - **CVS** (University Village): Look for sales and store-brand options.\n\n4. **Discount Stores**:  \n   - **Target** (University Village): Typically has affordable generic vitamins.  \n   - **Costco** (nearest location in South Lake Union): If you have a membership, Costco often has bulk vitamin B-12 at a lower per-unit cost.\n\n5. **Online Options**:  \n   If you're open to ordering online, **Amazon**, **Walmart**, or **iHerb** often have competitive prices and may offer delivery to your dorm or apartment.\n\n**Tips for Savings**:  \n- Look for store-brand or generic options, which are usually cheaper than name brands.  \n- Check for sales, coupons, or student discounts at local stores.  \n- Consider bulk purchasing if you use vitamin B-12 regularly.\n\nLet me know if you'd help finding specific deals or locations!",
